result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: The defendant has completed the required hours of Community Service.

10:14am Defendant Jessica J. Rude in court without counsel.  Gary King appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Advised of right to attorney and Constitutional rights. Defendant provides proof of community service completion and has paid all DAGP fines in full. State confirms. Court Dismisses the OTSC. DAGP successfully completed; dismiss per agreement.

Case called at 10:17 am.  Defendant Jessica J. Rude in court without counsel.  Loralee Clark appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  OTSC pending as the Defendant has not completed the terms of the agreement.  State requests that the DAGP be revoked.  Defendant requests time to complete 40 hours of community service and pay the fees. Court orders defendant to pay DAGP fees now and return to court with the receipt.
Case re-called at 10:23 am.  Defendant returns to court and indicates that she does not have the proper debit card with her to make payment today.
Court orders that all fees must be paid and community service must be completed by 6/26/18 or the DAGP will be revoked.    DPAH:  6/26/18 at 9:30 am.
Deferred prosecution agreement hearing on May 17, 2018 at 09:30 am.

Case called at 10:14 am. Defendant Jessica J. Rude in court without counsel.  Crystal Leigh Jensen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant advised of right to an attorney. Defendant indicates she did make payments but DA's office does not have record of the payments. She is working on her community service hours and thought she had until April 20th to complete the terms of the agreement.  Court extends DAGP to 5/17/18 at 9:30 am.

It is hereby Ordered that the defendant appear on 3/15/18 at 9:30 am and show cause why he/she should not be found guilty and sentenced for failure to comply with the Deferred Acceptance of a Guilty Plea Agreement.
Proposed Order to Show Cause
State's Petition to Show Cause
